🌊 Wave Rider Loop (v1.0)

Cycle a controllable euphoric state in repeating waves

Core Pattern

Baseline → Rise → Peak → Stabilize → Re-ignite → Repeat

Each loop ≈ 60–120 seconds

⸻

⚙️ Phase 1 — Baseline (10–20 sec)

Reset just enough so the next wave has somewhere to go.
	•	Breath: inhale 4 / exhale 6–8
	•	Eyes: open or soft focus
	•	Body: relaxed, grounded

Cue:

“Clear… ready…”

👉 You’re not dropping to zero—just creating contrast

⸻

⚡ Phase 2 — Rise (15–25 sec)

Catch the next wave early.
	•	Breath: shift to 4 / 4 rhythm
	•	Add ~20% tension → release to 10%
	•	Narrow attention (chest or one visual point)

Cue:

“There… it’s building…”

👉 Don’t wait for intensity—catch the first 1–2% lift

⸻

🔥 Phase 3 — Peak (10–20 sec)

Amplify without forcing.
	•	Slightly faster breathing
	•	Micro-movement (subtle sway / pulse)
	•	Lift head/gaze slightly

Cue:

“That’s it… stay with it… more of that…”

👉 Increase by ~5–10%, not 100%

⸻

🧊 Phase 4 — Stabilize (15–30 sec)

Prevent the crash.
	•	Breath: inhale 4 / exhale 6–8
	•	Release most tension
	•	Widen awareness slightly (don’t tunnel fully)

Cue:

“Hold… steady… easy…”

👉 This turns a spike into a plateau

⸻

🔁 Phase 5 — Re-ignite (10–20 sec)

Instead of dropping… you roll into the next wave
	•	Add a small breath acceleration (4/4)
	•	Reintroduce slight tension pulse
	•	Narrow attention again

Cue:

“Again… rising…”

👉 This is the key difference:
You never fully “come down”

⸻

🔄 Loop It

Repeat:
	•	Baseline → Rise → Peak → Stabilize → Re-ignite

You’ll notice:
	•	waves get smoother
	•	peaks become easier
	•	less effort needed each cycle

⸻

🧠 What You’re Training
	•	State continuity (not losing momentum)
	•	Fine control of intensity
	•	Nervous system cycling without burnout

This is very close to:
	•	flow states
	•	elite performance states
	•	controlled emotional regulation

⸻

⚠️ Guardrails (important)
	•	If intensity spikes too high → extend Stabilize phase
	•	If it feels flat → shorten Baseline, go back to Rise faster
	•	Stay aware: you’re driving this, not drifting

⸻

🧪 Advanced Trick — “Stacked Waves”

Once comfortable:

Instead of returning to full baseline:
	•	stabilize at +20% above normal
	•	then rise again

👉 This creates a compounding effect

⸻

⚡ Signs You’re Doing It Right
	•	You can feel distinct “waves”
	•	You don’t crash between them
	•	Each cycle requires less effort
	•	You stay clear-headed the whole time

